# Cursor Rules for Daniele Ligato Portfolio

## Project Overview
This is a **frontend-only** React portfolio website. It's a Single Page Application (SPA) with no backend server or database. All content is static and embedded in the code. Built with TypeScript, React, Vite, and Tailwind CSS.

## Entry Point & Execution Flow

### Execution Order:
1. **`index.html`** - Browser loads this first
   - Contains `<div id="root"></div>` where React renders
   - Has script tag: `<script type="module" src="/src/main.tsx"></script>`

2. **`src/main.tsx`** - This is the "main" function entry point
   - Uses `createRoot(document.getElementById("root")!)` to mount React
   - Renders `<App />` component: `.render(<App />)`
   - Imports CSS: `import "./index.css"`

3. **`src/App.tsx`** - Root React component
   - Sets up all providers: QueryClientProvider, TooltipProvider, BrowserRouter
   - Defines routes: `/` → Index, `*` → NotFound
   - This is where the React component tree starts

4. **`src/pages/Index.tsx`** - Home page component
   - Renders `<Layout>` wrapper
   - Contains: Hero, CompanyLogos, WorkExperience, Education, TechStack

